itools 0.62.6 (2011/01/XX)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.abnf             itools.i18n             itools.rss
  itools.core             itools.ical             itools.srx
  itools.csv              itools.log              itools.stl
  itools.database         itools.loop             itools.tmx
  itools.datatypes        itools.odf              itools.uri
  itools.fs               itools.office           itools.web
  itools.gettext          itools.pdf              itools.workflow
  itools.git              itools.pkg              itools.xliff
  itools.handlers         itools.python           itools.xml
  itools.html             itools.relaxng          itools.xmlfile
  itools.http             itools.rest

This release is about bug fixes and small features.

itools.core:
- Add the 'is_thingy' function.

itools.gettext:
- Now MSG is a thingy, and the boolean 'html' variable has been replaced
  by the more flexible 'format' variable:

    MSG(u'...', html=True)               # Before
    MSG(u'...', format='replace_html')   # Now

  The possible values of 'format' are: none, replace, html and replace_html.

itools.stl:
- Now the INFO & ERROR classes can contain STL, with format='stl'.

itools.web (bugs concerned: #878, #1044)
- Now the authentication cookie expires after 45min of inactivity.
- Include the user-agent in the authentication cookie.
- Send Last-Modified only for 200 and 304 responses.


